-Making sure someone has access to only authorized contants. A security best practice is least privilege which is giving rights and permissions only to what is needed.
-Mandatory Access Control (MAC): limit the access based on security clearance levels.
-Discretionary Access Control (DAC): the owner of the data decides who has access to the data.
-Role-Based Access Control (RBAC): depends on your role, a manager, director, team lead, project manager all have different rights.
-Rule-based Access Control: depends on predetermined rules.
-Attribute-Based Access Control (ABAC): access is based on different criteria set by the admin.
